  ${
    $d t x B $.  $d t x F $.  $d t x X $.  $d t x Y $.
    fgmin.1 $e |- X = U. B $.
    fgmin.2 $e |- Y = U. F $.
    $( Minimality property of a generated filter: every filter that contains
       ` B ` contains its generated filter.  (Contributed by Jeff Hankins,
       5-Sep-2009.) $)
    fgmin $p |- ( ( B e. fBas /\ F e. Fil /\ X = Y ) -> ( B C_ F <-> ( filGen `
    B ) C_ F ) ) $=
      ( vt vx cfbas wcel cfil wss wa cv wrex wb 3ad2ant1 adantr wi sylbid sseq2
      wceq w3a cfg cfv elfg 3ad2ant3 ssrexv adantl fillsb 3expd com34 r19.23adv
      ad2antlr syld com23 3adantl3 imp3a ssrdv ex fbssfg sstr2 syl impbid ) AIJ
